names based on the element <i>bud</i> ‘to inspire’ (from <i>buditi</i>), as for example <i>Budislav</i> ‘inspiring glory’."]}]},{"name":"Robert","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["One of the many French names of Germanic origin that were introduced into Britain by the Normans; it has since remained in continuous use. It is derived from the nearly synonymous elements <i>hrōd</i> ‘fame’ + <i>berht</i> ‘bright, famous’, and had a native Old English predecessor of similar form (<i>Hreodbeorht</i>), which was supplanted by the Norman name. Two dukes of Normandy in the 11th century bore the name: the father of  William the Conqueror  (sometimes identified with the legendary Robert the Devil), and his eldest son. It was borne also by three kings of Scotland, notably  Robert the Bruce  (  1274–1329 ), who freed Scotland from English domination. The altered short form <i>Bob</i> is very common, but <i>Hob</i> and <i>Dob</i>, which were common in the Middle Ages and gave rise to surnames, are extinct.  See also  Rupert ."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705201,"age":69,"year":"1549","julianDay":2286821,"title":"Book of Common Prayer","description":"Book of Common Prayer, a product of the English Reformation, was published in 1549 for assistance in the administration of the sacraments and other rites and ceremonies of the church according to the use of the Church of England. The book outlined morning, evening, and communion prayers and orders for baptism and marriage, thus making England a truly Protestant state.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Book_of_Common_Prayer","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Book of Common Prayer","jurisdictionLevel":0},{"id":1705202,"age":78,"year":"1558","julianDay":2290108,"title":"Act of Uniformity","description":"The Act of Uniformity was passed by the Parliament of England and required all people to go to church once a week. The consequence of not attending church was a fine of 12 pence, which was a considerable amount for a poor person.","jurisdictionLevel":0},{"id":1705206,"age":91,"year":"1571","julianDay":2294856,"title":"The Royal Exchange is Organized","description":"The Royal Exchange was organized in January 1571 by Sir Thomas Gresham. Gresham is known as the father of English banking.","jurisdictionLevel":0},{"id":1705207,"age":105,"year":"1585","julianDay":2299970,"title":"The First English Colony is Established in America","description":"England established its first colony in North America in 1585 as a way to generate additional wealth. The colony was named Virginia, after the virgin Queen Elizabeth I.","jurisdictionLevel":0}],"lifeSummary":"Robert Buchane was born in 1480, in England. He married Elizabeth in 1510, in England. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter."},"et":{"1480–":"1480–Surnud","1480–Female":"1480–Surnud","1506–1594":"1506–1594","1480–Male":"1480–Surnud","1558":"1558","1510":"1510","1585":"1585","1594":"1594","1571":"1571","1480":"1480","1506":"1506","1549":"1549","England":"England"},"fi":{"1480–":"1480–Kuollut","1480–Female":"1480–Kuollut","1506–1594":"1506–1594","1480–Male":"1480–Kuollut","1558":"1558","1510":"1510","1585":"1585","1594":"1594","1571":"1571","1480":"1480","1506":"1506","1549":"1549","England":"England"},"fr":{"1480–":"1480–Décédé","1480–Female":"1480–Décédée","1506–1594":"1506–1594","1480–Male":"1480–Décédé","1558":"1558","1510":"1510","1585":"1585","1594":"1594","1571":"1571","1480":"1480","1506":"1506","1549":"1549","England":"Angleterre","lifeSummary":"Robert Buchane est né en 1480, à Angleterre. Il a épousé Elizabeth en 1510, à Angleterre. Ils ont eu au moins 1 fille."},"de":{"1480–":"1480–Verstorben","1480–Female":"1480–Verstorben","1506–1594":"1506–1594","1480–Male":"1480–Verstorben","1558":"1558","1510":"1510","1585":"1585","1594":"1594","1571":"1571","1480":"1480","1506":"1506","1549":"1549","England":"England","lifeSummary":"Robert Buchane wurde 1480 i